data.Name: Tate McRae
data.Bio: Tatum Rosner "Tate" McRae (born July 1, 2003 in Calgary, Canada) is a Canadian singer, dancer and voice actress. At age 13, she gained prominence as the first Canadian finalist on the American reality TV show So You Think You Can Dance. McRae caught the attention of RCA Records in 2019 after her original song "One Day" went viral on YouTube, subsequently releasing her debut EP, All The Things I Never Said, in January 2020.
